$getFieldsNoData

$getFieldsNoData : boolean

Type

boolean — Indicate that `getFields()` and `getFieldsNoCache()` methods contain values or not. The result will be `true` if no value or no data, but will be `false` if there is at least a value or data.

generateKeyWithWaitTime()

generateKeyWithWaitTime(integer  $user_id, string  $keyFieldName, string  $timeFieldName, integer  $waitMinute = 10, array  $options = array()) : array

Generate key with wait time.

If the key was generated and still within wait time then it will be use the old one, otherwise it will be generate new.
This method did not create/update/delete the data in DB.

Parameters

integer $user_id

User ID.
string $keyFieldName

Name of field that contain key in field_value.
string $timeFieldName

Name of field that contain time in field_value.
integer $waitMinute

Minutes to wait.
array $options

The associative array options:
'keyLength' (int) The key length to generate. Default is 8.
'keyCharacters (string) The key string to generate. Default is empty string means 0-9, a-z.

update()

update(integer  $user_id, string  $field_name, mixed  $field_value, string|false|true  $field_description = false, mixed  $previousValue = false) : mixed

Update user field.

If data is not exists then it will be call add data automatically.

Parameters

integer $user_id

The user ID.
string $field_name

Field name.
mixed $field_value

Field value.
string|false|true $field_description

Field description. Set to false (default) to not change. Set to true to get it from registered fields data key and its description from rdbaUserFields property.
mixed $previousValue

Previous field value to check that it must be matched, otherwise it will not be update and return false. Set this to false to skip checking.

getFieldsNoCache()

getFieldsNoCache(integer  $objectId, string  $field_name = '') : mixed

Get meta fields data by conditions but no cache.

This method work the same as getFields() method but connect to DB without cache to make very sure that data is really exists.

Parameters

integer $objectId

The object ID.
string $field_name

The field name to search in. If this is empty then it will return all.

mixed —

Return a single row of field or all rows depend on field name to search. If it was not found then return null.
The return value may be unserialize if it is not scalar and not null.
You can call to property getFieldsNoData (boolean) to check that are there any data or value from this method.
